<chapter condition="TITLE=Services: Change Profile;ACCESS=SY_PROFILE"
         role="TOPIC">
  <title>Change Profile</title>

  <section condition="TITLE=Services: Change Profile;ACCESS=SY_PROFILE"
           role="ITEM">
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para role="TEXT">This module has just one function on the System Features
    menu, called <emphasis role="bold">Change Profile</emphasis>.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">All users can use the <application
    moreinfo="none">Change Profile</application> module to view and update
    their language and password. No particular jurisdiction is required to use
    this feature.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">When you click this function, you are presented with a
    form to update your profile.</para>
  </section>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Change Profile Form</title>

    <para role="TEXT">After entering your changes, click <emphasis
    role="bold">Save</emphasis> at the bottom of the form.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">When the password is changed, the password expiry date
    is computed and stored, and the invalid login attempts counter is
    reset.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">Depending on the system parameters, the new password may
    be checked against previously used passwords, and may be rejected. This
    prevents you simply re-using the same password.</para>

